<title>GridShib Certification Authority</title>

<sect1 id="welcome">
  <title>Welcome to Gridshib</title>
  <para>
    GridShib is a project to allow interoperability
    between <trademark class="registered">Globus Toolkit</trademark>
    and <trademark class="registered">Shibboleth</trademark>. Visit the
    GridShib web site
    (<ulink url="http://gridshib.globus.org/"/>)
    for more information about the GridShib Project.
  </para>
  <para>
    GridShib distributes four software components:
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem><para>GridShib for Globus Toolkit</para></listitem>
      <listitem><para>GridShib for Shibboleth</para></listitem>
      <listitem><para>GridShib Certificate Authority</para></listitem>
      <listitem><para>GridShib SAML Tools</para></listitem>	
    </itemizedlist>
  </para>
  <para>
    These software components help bridge the gap between SAML
    federations based on Shibboleth and Grid federations based on
    Globus Toolkit.  Visit
    the <ulink url="http://gridshib.globus.org/docs/gridshib/deploy-scenarios.html">GridShib
      Deployment Scenarios</ulink> to see how the various GridShib
    components might be used.
  </para>
</sect1>

<sect1 id="about">
  <title>About the GridShib-CA</title>
  <para>
    The GridShib-CA allows a user to authenticate using Shibboleth,
    and then creates and installs a short-lived Grid credential based
    on that authentication on the user's local system.  This
    credential is suitable for use with Grid Tools such as GT4.
  </para>
  <para>
    To use the GridShib CA you need to have
    <ulink url="http://java.sun.com/products/javawebstart/download.jsp">
      Java Web Start</ulink> installed on your system. A demonstration
    deployment of the GridShib-CA exists - see
    the <link linkend="test-deployment">section describing the test
      deployment</link> for details.
  </para>
</sect1>

